---
import { Icon } from "astro-icon";
import { Picture } from "@astrojs/image/components";

const skillSet = [
  {
    name: "HTML",
  },
  {
    name: "CSS",
  },
  {
    name: "Javascript",
  },
  {
    name: "TailwindCss",
  },
  {
    name: "Astro",
  },
  {
    name: "Typescript",
  },
];
---

<div class="prose md:text-xl text-center">
  <article class="text-black mb-8 min-w-fit">
    <h1 class="underline">Anime Database Search</h1>
    <Picture
      class="mb-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg"
      src="/images/JikanAPI.png"
      widths={[400, 600, 1024]}
      sizes="(max-width: 400px) 370px, (max-width: 600px) 600px, 1024px"
      aspectRatio="5:3"
      alt="Front End Portfolio"
      format="png"
      background="white"
    />
    <div class="flex justify-center">
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-3" name="React" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-3" name="Javascript" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-3" name="TailwindCss" />
      <a href="https://anime-api-xi.vercel.app/" target="_blank">
        <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="External" />
      </a>
    </div>
    <p>
      A React app I made using JikanAPI, which is a REST Api that contains
      information about shows from Japan. It contains a search function which
      brings back 15 shows alongside a synopsis and image, all pulled from the
      Api. It is also accompanied by an aside which contains the current Top Ten
      Shows, which changes depending on whatever is most popular at the time.
    </p>
  </article>

  <article class="text-black">
    <h1 class="underline">Pearl China</h1>
    <Picture
      class="mb-8 rounded-xl shadow-md"
      src="/images/PearlChina.png"
      widths={[400, 600, 1024]}
      sizes="(max-width: 400px) 370px, (max-width: 600px) 600px, 1024px"
      aspectRatio="5:3"
      alt="Pearl China"
      format="png"
      background="white"
    />
    <div class="flex justify-center">
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="HTML" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="CSS" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="Javascript" />
      <a href="https://pearlchina.co.uk/" target="_blank">
        <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="External" />
      </a>
    </div>
    <p>
      My first site that I deployed online was for a local business. It was a
      simple site that used some vanilla Javascript and had a Google Map embed
      in it. It is hosted on CloudFlare and gets a humble 700 vists a week.
    </p>
  </article>

  <article class="text-black mb-8 min-w-fit">
    <h1 class="underline">Blog Site/Portfolio</h1>
    <Picture
      class="mb-8 rounded-lg shadow-lg"
      src="/images/Portfolio.png"
      widths={[400, 600, 1024]}
      sizes="(max-width: 400px) 370px, (max-width: 600px) 600px, 1024px"
      aspectRatio="5:3"
      alt="Front End Portfolio"
      format="png"
      background="white"
    />
    <div class="flex justify-center">
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-3" name="HTML" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-3" name="Javascript" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-3" name="Typescript" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-3" name="Astro" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-3" name="TailwindCss" />
    </div>
    <p>
      My revamped portfolio site. My initial <a
        href="https://expressowl.github.io/Frontend-Portfolio/"
        class="hover:text-blue-500">one</a
      > had nice colors (in my opinion), but did not have the scalability of my current
      one that was made with Astro. I also wanted to challenge myself and use all
      the tech that I have learnt so far.
    </p>
  </article>

  <article class="text-black">
    <h1 class="underline">Initial Speed</h1>
    <Picture
      class="mb-8 rounded-xl shadow-md"
      src="/images/InitialSpeed.png"
      widths={[400, 600, 1024]}
      sizes="(max-width: 400px) 370px, (max-width: 600px) 600px, 1024px"
      aspectRatio="5:3"
      alt="Initial Speed"
      format="png"
      background="white"
    />
    <div class="flex justify-center">
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-3" name="HTML" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-3" name="TailwindCss" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-3" name="Javascript" />
      <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-3" name="Vite" />
      <a href="https://tailwind-website.onrender.com/" target="_blank">
        <Icon class="w-11 h-11 mx-4" name="External" />
      </a>
    </div>
    <p>
      A Mock up site for my friend's Skyline repair business. This was made with
      mobile in mind first and taught me the problems of having high quality
      images. They may look sweet but they take FOREVER to load if your user has
      a slow internet connection. I learnt about lazy loading and to adjust
      width and height of images so that you don't load more than you need to.
    </p>
  </article>

  <section class="text-black py-4 border-b last:border-t">
    <h1 class="underline">More Projects</h1>

    <div class="text-center">
      <a
        href="https://github.com/ExpressOwl"
        target="_blank"
        class="inline-block m-auto text-center text-3xl bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-500 to-pink-500 px-2 py-4 cursor-pointer transition-all hover:shadow-md"
        >Visit my GitHub</a
      >
    </div>

    <p>
      If you visit my GitHub you can see some of the more mundane projects, such
      as creating a toast message, making a pomodoro timer and making a ReactJS
      countdown app.
    </p>
  </section>
</div>
